{"questionId":"11131","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Proteins have structural or enzyme functions.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Oil spills are a major environmental problem.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Suggest <strong>two</strong> reasons why oil decomposes faster at the surface of the ocean than at greater depth.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Any two of:</em><br>surface water is warmer «so faster reaction rate»/more light/energy from the sun <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">more oxygen «for aerobic bacteria/oxidation of oil»&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">greater surface area&nbsp;<strong style=\"color:#000000;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-size:14px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;white-space:normal;\">[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11131","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.6c(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Suggest two reasons why oil decomposes faster at the surface of the ocean than at greater depth.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.6 Biochemistry and the environment","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}